# VetSteady — Environment Variables

Copy this to `.env.local` and fill in your values.

```env
# ─── Supabase ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# Direct Postgres URI for pg-boss (from Supabase → Settings → Database → Connection string → URI)
# Use the "connection pooling" URI with ?pgbouncer=true removed — pg-boss needs persistent connections
SUPABASE_DB_URL=postgresql://postgres.your-project:your-db-password@aws-0-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres

# ─── Twilio ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-auth-token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+15551234567

# ─── Resend (email) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=reminders@vetsteady.com

# ─── Stripe ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxxxxxxxxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxx
STRIPE_STARTER_PRICE_ID=price_xxxxxxxxxxxx    # $30/mo Starter plan
STRIPE_PRO_PRICE_ID=price_xxxxxxxxxxxx        # $49/mo Pro plan

# ─── App ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://vetsteady.com      # no trailing slash
CRON_SECRET=generate-a-random-secret-here      # used to auth /api/cron/* routes

# ─── PostHog Analytics ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from app.posthog.com → Project Settings
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=phc_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://app.posthog.com   # or your self-hosted URL
```

## Setup Steps

1. Create a Supabase project at supabase.com
2. Run `supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql` in the SQL editor
3. Run `supabase/migrations/002_reminder_engine.sql` in the SQL editor
4. Fill in `.env.local` above
5. `npm install && npm run dev`
6. Deploy to Vercel — add all env vars in Vercel dashboard
7. Set Twilio SMS webhook URL: `https://vetsteady.com/api/webhooks/twilio`

## pg-boss Notes

pg-boss creates its own `pgboss` schema in your Postgres DB on first run.
The `SUPABASE_DB_URL` must be a **direct** connection string (not a pgBouncer pooler URL),
as pg-boss requires persistent connections for advisory locks.

Use the **Session mode** pooler URI from Supabase (port 5432) or the direct connection (port 5432).
Avoid Transaction mode pooler (port 6543) — it breaks pg-boss.
